I"<p><a href="http://ngcc.sbsm.gov.cn/article/en/ls/cj/">Chen Jun</a>, Chief Scientist of the National Geomatics Centre of China (NGCC) and <a href="http://www.isprs.org/structure/council.aspx">ISPRS First Vice President</a> visited the 3D geoinformation group on 4 November 2016. He discussed on-going projects with several researchers of the group, and expressed interest in establishing research cooperation with the Delft University of Technology. Chen Jun received a memory stick with the demo and information about our group. During this visit Chen Jun and Sisi Zlatanova discussed the activities of the <a href="http://www2.isprs.org/commissions/comm4.html">ISPRS Commission IV</a> in support of the <a href="https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/?menu=1300">UN Inter-agency Expert Group on Sustainable Development Goals Indicators</a> with a working Group on Geospatial Information. Chen Jun is nominated as the representative of the Asia-Pacific region in the Expert Group.</p>

